10/29/2018
Why Roosevelt did not tell America
by: Philo
edit
After the Nazis were effectively defeated US forces came across the extermination death camps. Censored pictures of emaciated survivors and piles of dead. The world was shocked. But, Churchill and Roosevelt knew about the death camps for a long time. You'd think they would have used this unspeakably horrific program as a propaganda weapon. But, truth was they we're afraid of the public reaction. They worried that a large portion of their citizens might actually secretly approve and news about the genocide of the Jews campaign might actually sway them in favor of Germany.

Hatred of the Jews has been a feature of human history since as far back as you can go. The Jews first appear on the scene when they were exiled from Egypt. Next the Persians raided their lands and led them off in captivity. (It was during the Babylonian exile when stories about the flood and the tower and the garden and the apple and the snake entered the Hebrew lexicon). After Alexander conquered Persia a city he built on the far side of the Nile delta became the most prominent intellectual cultural center in the western world. Like they say about New York today where more Jews live than in Israel, more Jews lived in Alexandria Egypt. Soon the first recorded pogroms started taking place. First the native Egyptian populous and the Macedonians who called themselves Greeks, later the Romans, then the Christians and eventually the Muslims all persecuted the Jews in Alexandria and wherever they tried to live. In medieval Europe the Jews were consistently pushed further and farer east into Poland and then the Black forest the Ukrainian wilderness known as the Pale. Then beyond the Pale.

What is it About Jews?

What is that causes EVERYBODY to hate the Jews? I have some blood of tribe in me and I think I can feel it. I have blue eyes and (had) blond hair and a anglicized name so I can "pass" as a total gentile. And yet all my life I have sensed there's just something about me. People just find something about me alien, uncomfortable. No one has ever just come up to me and said Hi. I talk to people and try to make friends, but there's just something missing. No connection.
Jews don't even like me. Judaism is a matriarchal blood lineage designation. When a Jewish man marries a blue eyed blonde gentile the woman is called a Shiksa in Yiddish. Their offspring are not considered Jewish. An Israeli soldier who dies in battle, is buried in a different cemetery if her mother is a gentile. Not even good Jewish girls will have anything to do with me. My father was a Jew but not my blonde and blue mother. So, I exhibit all sorts of Jewish traits such as high intelligence; just enough to make me repellent to red necks, not enough to make me acceptable to the Jewish community.
I live in Texas. After over thirty years no one confuses me as a Texan. The first thing I hear when I do talk to somebody new is "Where you from?" I'm from New Jersey. My children are native Texans and I don't even get along well with me. I haven't seen my daughter in many years and my son is a Ted Cruz conservative. I try but sometimes I can't conceal my disappointment.
That's a Jewish trait. I can just say hello to someone but from the tone of my voice or some subtle uncontrollable facial tick, what people hear when I say hello or anything is: I think you're stupid. I pity you. I think I'm above you. And people hate that more than anything. The principle reason conservatives hate liberals is the intolerable sense that we are condescending.
There is nothing that irritates a person more than to perceive the sense they are being condescended to. NOTHING. Nothing raises the hackles of a conservative is that sense that liberals think they're smarter than they are, that they think they're better. Nothing pleases a conservative more than finding a way to poke liberals in the eye. Conservatives will support a policy they know is harmful to the environment or detrimental to the general wellbeing if they think it will outrage and upset liberals. It's all a reaction to that feeling that someone looks down on you.

10/29/2018
Why Roosevelt did not tell America
by: Philo
edit
After the Nazis were effectively defeated US forces came across the extermination death camps. Censored pictures of emaciated survivors and piles of dead. The world was shocked. But, Churchill and Roosevelt knew about the death camps for a long time. You'd think they would have used this unspeakably horrific program as a propaganda weapon. But, truth was they we're afraid of the public reaction. They worried that a large portion of their citizens might actually secretly approve and news about the genocide of the Jews campaign might actually sway them in favor of Germany.

Hatred of the Jews has been a feature of human history since as far back as you can go. The Jews first appear on the scene when they were exiled from Egypt. Next the Persians raided their lands and led them off in captivity. (It was during the Babylonian exile when stories about the flood and the tower and the garden and the apple and the snake entered the Hebrew lexicon). After Alexander conquered Persia a city he built on the far side of the Nile delta became the most prominent intellectual cultural center in the western world. Like they say about New York today where more Jews live than in Israel, more Jews lived in Alexandria Egypt. Soon the first recorded pogroms started taking place. First the native Egyptian populous and the Macedonians who called themselves Greeks, later the Romans, then the Christians and eventually the Muslims all persecuted the Jews in Alexandria and wherever they tried to live. In medieval Europe the Jews were consistently pushed further and farer east into Poland and then the Black forest the Ukrainian wilderness known as the Pale. Then beyond the Pale.

What is it About Jews?

What is that causes EVERYBODY to hate the Jews? I have some blood of tribe in me and I think I can feel it. I have blue eyes and (had) blond hair and a anglicized name so I can "pass" as a total gentile. And yet all my life I have sensed there's just something about me. People just find something about me alien, uncomfortable. No one has ever just come up to me and said Hi. I talk to people and try to make friends, but there's just something missing. No connection.
Jews don't even like me. Judaism is a matriarchal blood lineage designation. When a Jewish man marries a blue eyed blonde gentile the woman is called a Shiksa in Yiddish. Their offspring are not considered Jewish. An Israeli soldier who dies in battle, is buried in a different cemetery if her mother is a gentile. Not even good Jewish girls will have anything to do with me. My father was a Jew but not my blonde and blue mother. So, I exhibit all sorts of Jewish traits such as high intelligence; just enough to make me repellent to red necks, not enough to make me acceptable to the Jewish community.
I live in Texas. After over thirty years no one confuses me as a Texan. The first thing I hear when I do talk to somebody new is "Where you from?" I'm from New Jersey. My children are native Texans and I don't even get along well with me. I haven't seen my daughter in many years and my son is a Ted Cruz conservative. I try but sometimes I can't conceal my disappointment.
That's a Jewish trait. I can just say hello to someone but from the tone of my voice or some subtle uncontrollable facial tick, what people hear when I say hello or anything is: I think you're stupid. I pity you. I think I'm above you. And people hate that more than anything. The principle reason conservatives hate liberals is the intolerable sense that we are condescending.
There is nothing that irritates a person more than to perceive the sense they are being condescended to. NOTHING. Nothing raises the hackles of a conservative is that sense that liberals think they're smarter than they are, that they think they're better. Nothing pleases a conservative more than finding a way to poke liberals in the eye. Conservatives will support a policy they know is harmful to the environment or detrimental to the general wellbeing if they think it will outrage and upset liberals. It's all a reaction to that feeling that someone looks down on you.
